properties.areaDesc: East Entrance U.S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 21 at 2:38PM PST until January 23 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, southeast winds 25 to 35 kt. For
the Small Craft Advisory, southeast winds 20 to 30 kt.

* WHERE...East Entrance U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 7 PM PST this evening. For
the Small Craft Advisory, from 1 PM Wednesday to 4 AM PST
Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Warning means winds of 34 to 47 knots are imminent or
occurring. Operating a vessel in gale conditions requires
experience and properly equipped vessels. It is highly
recommended that mariners without the proper experience seek safe
harbor prior to the onset of gale conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM WEDNESDAY TO 4 AM PST THURSDAY
